tip.text: Thai beef salad is good, but skip the rice paper rolls and the banana tapioca dessert. Average prices. The venue is quite nice, with quick service. Food could overall be more flavourful and authentic.
Brunch food is honestly very basic and nothing to rave about. Good French toast and fresh coconut. Come for the very bright and relaxing venue. Booking further ahead is mandatory.
Hip and beautiful place, pretty loud music. Sea bream classic ceviche is so tasty! Get a few plates to share. Cocktails look nice too.
Food is quite good, but I am slightly disappointed with the too soft noodles, the not that flavourful bao filling, and the bit dry guo kui filling. The venue is bright and nice. No queue.
Bad service and less than average food. Skip dessert. Tuna starter is quite good though.
Les macarons sont divins et font sérieusement concurrence aux plus grands noms. Testé et approuvé : cassis et citron vert. / Delicious macarons, don't miss it!
Dishes are just ok, not particularly tasty and not the best quality. Prices are quite cheap though. Nothing to rave about here.
Authentic French food, big portions and low prices, but not the best quality. Fast service, no reservations. It's ok if you want to try some typical Basque/French food.
Authentic and prepared by Japanese people. Sushi rice is good, however I expected better fish. A bit expensive. Very quiet place.
A great spa room. Tea room is bright, comfy and so cosy! Service is great. I loved the homemade madeleines that came with my tea.
Good quality French food here! Short but appealing menu (nice burgers). Excellent value for money. Be sure to book ahead. A great restaurant for the area.

formattedAddress: 48 rue du Dessous des Berges (31 rue Cantagrel)

tip.text: Good quality French food here! Short but appealing menu (nice burgers). Excellent value for money. Be sure to book ahead. A great restaurant for the area.

formattedAddress: 48 rue du Dessous des Berges (31 rue Cantagrel)

tip.text: Tiramisu is DELISH, save some space for it! Any of the pasta dishes is excellent. A large preference for the room at the back, beautiful and bright thanks to the glass roof.
Great cocktails and nice terrace. Perfect for aperitivo. Standard prices.
Delicious and very creative cocktails. Not expensive. The venue is extremely crowded and it makes it hard to get a seat.
Great customisable coffee: chocolate, hazelnut... Nice venue and sunny terrace.
Shrimp papaya salad is good. Avoid dumplings, almost no filling and reheated. Chicken in the bo bun is bad (not homemade). Small venue without any charm.
Food is extremely greasy and lacks of flavour, a big disappointment. Lamb skewers are good though (but not Chinese...). Extensive and cheap menu.
The ingredients' quality is great and everything is well executed. However, there is a lack of flavours and coherence in the dishes. Good value for money, but slightly disappointing. No reservations.
Italian owner and staff. Great quality food, perfect service and cosy venue. Don't miss their homemade ice cream for dessert, they are all divine!
They have bubble tea: milk tea tastes like water, however tapioca pearls are very good.
Pastries are huge and not too expensive, but not made with quality ingredients. It still tastes ok.
Decent food but expensive. Tiramisu is bad, and not authentic at all. Service is very fast, and the place is bright and loud.

French bistro with a short food menu (meat, fish and salads) and decent food. Portions are quite large, especially the café gourmand. Crumble is good. A bit expensive but there's not much in the area.
Pancakes are seriously out of this world!! Interesting flavours in their dishes. Cramped venue and inefficient service: you have to queue at the counter every time you want to order something.
Pastries are not that well executed and are disappointing considering their price (the famous Mont-Blanc is quite heavy). However, you'll enjoy the brightness of the venue.

formattedAddress: Musée du Luxembourg (19 rue de Vaugirard)

tip.text: DIY salads with a large choice of quite good ingredients. Portions are big. Large offer of freshly made desserts. There are a few tables to eat inside, but the venue is basic.
Menu is short but well-executed. Food is really authentic (great minced pork), and bubble tea is among the best in Paris. Service is nice and quick.

contact.facebookName: MOMO 茶 Salon de Thé Taïwanais

tip.text: Great brunch food, creative and well executed. French toast is amazingly good! Cosy place - a bit cramped - and cool vibe. You'll have to queue for an hour at least though. A tad expensive.
Ramen here is miso or soy based, don't expect the classic pork broth. Ingredients are ok, minced pork tastes weird and bamboo was a bit smelly... Gyozas are very good. Opened late.
La Fruitière restaurant: tasty and great quality food, super friendly staff and efficient service. The terrace view on the mountains is outstanding. Expensive but totally worth it.
You can choose your ingredients (pretty large choice and good quality) and sauce to compose your own salad. Average size salad for 5.5€. There are a few tables outside, perfect to catch the sun!
Decent food: good andouillette, OK beef tartare, bad fries. Lemon tart dessert is excellent though. Staff could be nicer and more efficient. Prices a bit high, but nice sunny terrace.
Simple yet modern venue. Dishes are overall good quality, nicely presented and taste like proper Korean food. I recommend the spicy octopus! Prices are a bit high though.
Wine is excellent, and you can feel the staff is really knowledgeable about it. Charcuterie is very good too. A special mention for the super nice and friendly waiters.
Very good and delicate pastries, especially the Pear and the Vanilla-Almond tart. They have a small tea room but you might have to wait a bit. Also try their delicious homemade spreads!
Unlimited food for 12€ on evenings, disappointing: you can't choose your dumplings' flavours. Noodle bowls are good, however noodles are not homemade. The venue is really cramped and not so nice.

Very good Indian food - get the Massala chicken. You can let the waiters know you like spicy food and they will adjust the taste of your dishes. The venue is cosy and very nice. Prices are a bit high.
Their bread and viennoiseries rank among the best I ever had. Chausson aux pommes, any of the roulés... Be prepared to queue though. I'd be back everyday if I could!
Pastry shop with a cosy and quiet small tea room. Pastries are exquisite, especially the Kara Damia. Chocolate lovers should try the hot chocolate tart soufflé (onsite only). This place won my heart!
The venue is quite cramped; you'll have to queue but it's moving fast. Bo bun is ok: it could contain more flavourful herbs, and the beef is a bit hard. They do have milk tea just like in Asia.
Quality food with an excellent value for money, especially at lunch time. Every dish is delicate and full of flavours. The venue is nice and cosy. I strongly recommend to book ahead.
Small but interesting offer of healthy dishes, made with quality ingredients. Tiramisu is very good! The venue has a nice vibe, and staff is friendly. Overall a bit expensive for what you get though.

formattedAddress: 32 rue de la Fontaine au Roi
location.address: 32 rue de la Fontaine au Roi

tip.text: Don't expect authentic Thai food. Massaman curry is NOT a proper Massaman curry. Curries are globally very heavy, and sticky rice is awfully overcooked. The venue is quite nice, but it was empty.

formattedAddress: 32 rue de la Fontaine au Roi
location.address: 32 rue de la Fontaine au Roi

tip.text: Decent food: BBQ chicken is quite good, but too expensive. The venue is simple without any charm. Waitresses barely speak French.
Very small and intimate venue, Italian owners. They serve homemade fresh pasta dishes, so good and authentic! Tiramisu is good with a strong coffee flavour. Be sure to book ahead.
Burgers, tartares and grilled meat cuts of your choice. Good value for money. Seating is quite rustic. Beware, there is no ventilation so you'll leave with a strong food smell on your clothes.
Enjoyable tea room. Try the Paris-Brest, it has praline ganache hidden inside the cream. Hot chocolate is quite good but not warm enough, I had better.
Cramped and noisy, it felt so hot upstairs! Nice selection of teas and homemade cakes. My verdict on the cheesecake: light (wish it was creamier) with a soggy crust, overall quite good.

formattedAddress: 8 rue Saint-Martin (Square de la Tour Saint-Jacques)

tip.text: The red meat is great, especially the Black Angus "hampe". Pommes dauphines are really tasty too. Desserts: don't miss the crème brûlée! Tiramisu is quite good. Small place, better to book ahead.
Good and authentic Chinese dumplings, steamed or grilled. The venue is clean and sober. They take reservations.
They make a decent cappuccino. Cosy and bright venue, very enjoyable.
Not the best raw fish I ever tasted, but it's decent. Seaweed salad is very good. The venue is comfy and cosy.
If you're French you'll be disappointed by their croissant. Chocolate is good though. There's a small seating area at the back of the shop.
Japanese canteen serving a large choice of authentic dishes. Prices are quite cheap. You'll need to queue but it's moving fast. Toridon was really nice!
Come in the afternoon for tea time, and get Pierre Hermé pastries. Comfortable and cosy.
Delicious small plates. Order baos and the trotter nuggets. Come after 2pm on weekdays and you won't need to queue! Overall not cheap.
Chocolate cookie is delicious!
Great coffee. Cosy venue, good for working.

contact.facebookName: L'Atelier Joël Robuchon - Paris Saint Germain
L'Atelier Joël Robuchon - Paris Saint Germain
L'Atelier Joël Robuchon - Paris Saint Germain
L'Atelier Joël Robuchon - Paris Saint Germain
L'Atelier Joël Robuchon - Paris Saint Germain

tip.text: Everything is excellent. You can choose to order several small plates instead of a single main (get the lamb cutlets). Seating at the bar table is cosy and enjoyable. No reservations. Expensive place.

contact.facebookName: L'Atelier Joël Robuchon - Paris Saint Germain

tip.text: Brunch 7/7 24h. Ricotta pancakes are the highlight. Hot chocolate is also excellent. No reservation, but no queue on weekdays.
Delicious and authentic Sichuan food. Get dumplings and the Sichuan beef noodle soup! Careful on the spice's level, you can choose from 0 to 5 but 0.5 is already quite spicy.

contact.facebookName: Trois Fois Plus De Piment - restaurant de Sichuan

tip.text: Best Liège waffles (the thick ones) to take away!
My salad was ok. The venue is really not enjoyable, unless you sit on the terrace. Friendly and accommodating waiters.
Delicious and authentic Thai food (yummy pad-Thai & green curry). Portions are cheap but on the small side. Pretty packed venue and always crowded, be sure to book ahead.
Overall good food but totally overpriced. Desserts are a bit disappointing. The childhood-themed decoration is nice though. Other restaurants in the area offer a better price-quality ratio.
Big French brasserie serving quality comforting food at fair prices. Thai beef salad (14€) is very tasty. A special mention to the Nutella tiramisu, heaven (and not heavy at all)!
Typical French dishes from the region. Great food quality and friendly (but a bit long) service. Get the "ravioles aux cèpes", so tasty! Beef tartare and entrecôte are great, and fries are homemade.
Fine food at affordable prices (~25€ for a main dish). Service is excellent. Quiet venue, which could be nicer though. I recommend the duck dish, so good! Desserts are not as good as the rest.
Their vanilla millefeuille is the best I ever had, oh so flavourful vanilla cream & light puff pastry. Tasty selection of chocolates coming in gorgeous boxes (great for a gift!). Cosy tea room.
Delicious pork belly bao! Good value for money. You'll probably queue during peak hours.
Hands down to THE BEST tiramisu I had in Paris so far. Pasta dishes are quite good. Overall authentic, however service could be more friendly.

formattedAddress: 21 rue Juliette Dodu (Rue de Sambre et Meuse)

tip.text: Quality viennoiseries and pastries. Beautiful shop, prices are quite high as expected. Great for special occasions - you can order online on their website.
Quality meat, tender and juicy with a smoky taste. Excellent desserts as well. Service is good, and the venue is bright and trendy. Prices can get a bit high for the best meat cuts.
Fancy pastry shop and quite expensive. I got a chocolate & meringue pastry: too dry, could be tastier.
Not authentic, however some flavours are nice. Disappointing if you've already had dim sum in Asia. Quite expensive considering the portions.
Incredible dining experience at this 3 Michelin stars restaurant, specialised in vegetables cooking. Every dish is gorgeous and so tasty. The venue is bright and quiet (ask for the main room).
Pastries all look divine! I tried "Le Galet", gorgeous and delicious. There is a tearoom to have cakes on-site.
Modern Korean food with sharing plates concept. Trendy & cosy, fast service. Korean fried chicken is very good. Lunch menu is nice and worth it. I will be back to try their cocktails on the evening.
Great brunch (single menu: 33€). Viennoiseries and all 3 dishes are excellent. Service is quick and efficient, place is nicely decorated and trendy. Be sure to book.

Cosy venue, good for dates. Food is excellent: order croquettas, yellowtail carpaccio, oxtail & pluma Iberico. Overall quite expensive but worth the money. Service is efficient but slightly intrusive.
Excellent runny scrambled eggs with avocado toast, great coffee. Gorgeous plates and nice staff that however seemed over-busy. Quinoa pancakes tasted weird to me. Chill vibe.
Excellent value for money. If you like your steak rare, ask for blue. Eggplant side is very good. Try not to come on evenings as the queue is really long.
Fine and delicate food prepared by a Japanese chef. Two lunch sets to choose from. I definitely recommend the Wagyu beef! The place is minimalist with a nice and discrete service.

The highlight is the noodle soup with fresh handmade noodles ("lamian"). The broth is rich and hearty. Grilled dumplings are quite good but could be tastier. Canteen-like place, fast and nice service.
Large offer of freshly baked cookies (they have an on-site oven). Ask for the warm ones! A bit expensive, but cookies are amazingly gooey, a must-have for any cookie lover.
Amazingly tasty spring rolls!! I would return only to have these. Good bo bun, but it could be a bit more herb-flavoured. Get the marinated shrimps one, yum!
Exceptional: great products quality and perfect cooking mastery. Friendly and cosy. Île flottante for dessert is the best I ever had! Be sure to book ahead.
Exceptional: quality products, perfect cooking mastery and beautiful plates. Friendly owners, but slow service. White chocolate & olive cookie is divine! Small place, book ahead (lunch and dinner).
Incredibly tasty vegetables spring rolls! Pad Thai was good but lacked a bit of taste. Nice service.
Authentic and quality Chinese food. Baozi are incredibly tasty, so is the aubergine dish. Best baozi I had outside Asia so far! Strongly recommend.
Dumplings are slightly overcooked and the filling does not have much flavour. Ice milk tea is bad. Disappointing compared to Chinese standards.
Excellent savoury crepes dough with a crispy texture. Large selection of delicious sweet crepes. If you like the combination chocolate-orange, I strongly recommend L'Orange Noire! Be sure to book.
Summer menu 2016: get the gazpacho (fabulous) and the milk chocolate & coconut dessert. Then you can thank me! 😉
Every plate was beautiful and tasty. Fish was cooked to perfection, dry aged rib steak was outstanding. Nice atmosphere and staff. I strongly recommend!
Araignée as a starter was excellent. My fish was overcooked, but the truffle mashed potatoes was very good. Chocolate fondant and lemon tart for dessert are must have. Overall pricy.
Authentic specialties of Corsica. Both veal (sauté de veau) and wild boar (daube de sanglier) dishes were excellent. The small room at the back of the restaurant has a very nice view, I recommend.
Very good food, especially the pastas with lobster. Risotto was overcooked. Everything else was excellent, but pricy.
Large selection of teas to have hot or cold. The place is small but cosy. I really liked the mango madness tea served cold.

location.address: G/F, 21 Ormsby Street, Tung Lo Wan Road, Tai Hang, Tai Hang
formattedAddress: G/F, 21 Ormsby Street, Tung Lo Wan Road, Tai Hang, Tai Hang

tip.text: Very good dim sum, especially the shrimp dumplings and custard buns. Cheap prices.
Great beef noodle soup! Be prepared to queue a bit as the place is quite famous. Really cheap.
Good sashimi set. Small and quiet place. Lunch deals are worth it.
Excellent mango mochi and mango juice!

venue.name: E-Hap Dessert House 二合甜館

tip.text: Restaurant frequented by locals. Excellent dim sum, reasonably priced. Clean place.

formattedAddress: Unit CF11, Queen Street Cooked Food Market, 1/F, 38 Des Voeux Rd W

venue.name: Traditional Beijing Dumpling House 老北方餃子館

tip.text: Loved the atmosphere, especially the open terrace on 1st floor. Food is very good (confit lamb shoulder and profiterole for dessert). Cocktails are delicious. I'll be back!
Nice macarons, creamier and more buttery than the French ones. Gianduja e lemone was very good! Good coffee as well.

formattedAddress: Aeroporto di Bergamo - Orio al Serio (BGY) (Piano 1)
location.address: Aeroporto di Bergamo - Orio al Serio (BGY)

tip.text: Large range of amazing pastries for dessert. They all are truly marvellous, I like to come there only for the cakes. Highlights were Inaya lulo & Cherry chocolate.
Large selection of sourdough bread and pastries. AMAZING raspberry financier!
Don't miss the Dumpling Shack stall!

venue.name: SAID dal 1923 Antica Fabbrica del Cioccolato Roma

tip.text: Good quality chocolate, but hot chocolate tastes like chocolate sauce and is too heavy. Cramped place and speedy service. Truffles are really good though.

venue.name: SAID dal 1923 Antica Fabbrica del Cioccolato Roma

tip.text: Food has outstanding flavours. I strongly recommend the octopus and sea bass dishes. Service was excellent and the venue (upstairs) is bright and cosy.
